1
00:00:55,388 --> 00:00:58,932
Pull yourself together, Teddy.
Pull yourself together.

2
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:07,024
It's just water.

3
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:10,193
It's a lot of water.

4
00:01:10,737 --> 00:01:12,237
A lot of...

5
00:01:15,783 --> 00:01:17,159
Come on.

6
00:01:41,225 --> 00:01:44,353
- You okay, boss?
- Yeah, I'm fine, I just...

7
00:01:45,313 --> 00:01:48,231
I just can't... Can't stomach the water.

8
00:01:51,736 --> 00:01:54,404
- You're my new partner.
- That's right.

9
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:58,492
Not the best way to meet,
with my head halfway down the toilet.

10
00:01:58,576 --> 00:02:01,620
Doesn't exactly square with
"Teddy Daniels, the man, the legend,"

11
00:02:01,704 --> 00:02:04,164
- I'll give you that.
- The legend?

12
00:02:04,248 --> 00:02:06,917
What the hell you boys smoking
over there in Portland, anyway?

13
00:02:07,001 --> 00:02:10,379
Seattle. I came from
the office in Seattle.

14
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:15,258
How long you been with the Marshals?

15
00:02:15,343 --> 00:02:16,760
Four years.

16
00:02:18,346 --> 00:02:20,681
So you know how small it is.

17
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:22,182
Sure.

18
00:02:23,226 --> 00:02:26,186
What about you?
You got a girl? Married?

19
00:02:27,021 --> 00:02:28,271
I was.

20
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:41,743
She died.

21
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:45,706
- Jesus. I don't...
- Don't worry about it.

22
00:02:46,749 --> 00:02:50,335
There was a fire at the apartment
building while I was at work.

23
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:52,129
Four people died.

24
00:02:52,213 --> 00:02:56,049
It was the smoke that got her,
not the fire. See, that's important.

25
00:02:56,134 --> 00:02:57,843
I'm sorry, boss.

26
00:02:57,927 --> 00:03:00,721
Where are my goddamn cigarettes?

27
00:03:00,805 --> 00:03:02,889
Oh, here, have one of mine.

28
00:03:02,974 --> 00:03:06,476
I could've sworn they were
in my jacket before I got on.

29
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:09,271
Government employees
will rob you blind.

30
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:12,941
Thanks.

31
00:03:13,985 --> 00:03:16,737
They give you a briefing about
the institution before you left?

32
00:03:16,821 --> 00:03:19,489
All I know is it's a mental hospital.

33
00:03:20,324 --> 00:03:22,451
For the criminally insane.

34
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:25,620
Well, if it's just folks running
around hearing voices

35
00:03:25,705 --> 00:03:29,166
and chasing after butterflies,
they wouldn't need us.

36
00:03:38,342 --> 00:03:41,178
- Is that where we're headed?
- Yep.

37
00:03:41,679 --> 00:03:44,055
The other side of the island
is rock bluffs

38
00:03:44,140 --> 00:03:46,683
all the way down
to the edge of the water.

39
00:03:46,768 --> 00:03:50,228
The dock, it's the only way on or off.

40
00:03:51,314 --> 00:03:54,274
We'll be casting off
as soon as you two are ashore.

41
00:03:54,358 --> 00:03:56,985
I'd appreciate it if you'd hurry up about it.

42
00:03:57,069 --> 00:03:59,821
- Why?
- Storm's coming.

43
00:04:26,224 --> 00:04:28,850
Never seen a Marshals badge before.

44
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,395
I'm Deputy Warden McPherson,
gentlemen.

45
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:33,647
Welcome to Shutter Island.

46
00:04:33,731 --> 00:04:36,775
I'll be the one taking you
up to Ashecliffe.

47
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,957
Your boys seem a little on edge,
Mr. McPherson.

48
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:54,417
Right now, Marshal, we all are.

49
00:05:38,462 --> 00:05:40,714
Electrified perimeter.

50
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:44,301
How can you tell?

51
00:05:44,635 --> 00:05:47,220
I've seen something like it before.

52
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:19,669
All right. You gentlemen will
be accorded all the help we can give,

53
00:06:19,754 --> 00:06:22,714
but during your stay,
you will obey protocol.

54
00:06:22,798 --> 00:06:24,174
Is that understood?

55
00:06:24,258 --> 00:06:25,634
Absolutely.

56
00:06:26,093 --> 00:06:29,429
The red brick building on your right
is Ward A, the male ward.

57
00:06:29,513 --> 00:06:32,891
Ward B, the female ward,
is the one on your left.

58
00:06:32,975 --> 00:06:35,936
Ward C is that building on the bluffs.

59
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:37,604
An old Civil War fort.

60
00:06:37,688 --> 00:06:40,106
The most dangerous patients
are housed there.

61
00:06:40,191 --> 00:06:42,108
Admittance to Ward C is forbidden

62
00:06:42,193 --> 00:06:44,861
without the written consent
and physical presence

63
00:06:44,946 --> 00:06:47,489
of both myself and Dr. Cawley.

64
00:06:47,573 --> 00:06:49,366
Is that understood?

65
00:06:50,326 --> 00:06:52,744
You act like insanity is catching.

66
00:06:55,623 --> 00:06:58,875
You are hereby required
to surrender your firearms.

67
00:07:00,378 --> 00:07:03,755
Mr. McPherson, we are duly appointed
federal marshals.

68
00:07:03,839 --> 00:07:06,341
We are required to carry our firearms
with us at all times.

69
00:07:06,425 --> 00:07:09,427
Executive order 319
of the Federal Code of Penitentiaries

70
00:07:09,512 --> 00:07:11,554
states that when inside a penitentiary,

71
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:15,058
the officers of that institution
have final authority.

72
00:07:17,937 --> 00:07:21,940
Gentlemen, you will not get through
this gate with your firearms.

73
00:07:41,377 --> 00:07:44,671
Okay. Now that the official stuff's done,
come on, boys,

74
00:07:44,755 --> 00:07:46,715
what do you say we go find Dr. Cawley?

75
00:07:58,769 --> 00:08:01,438
When did she escape? This prisoner?

76
00:08:01,522 --> 00:08:05,692
I'm afraid Dr. Cawley will have
to fill you in on the situation. Protocol.

77
00:08:05,776 --> 00:08:07,902
Correctional officers
at a mental institution,

78
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:10,155
that's a weird sight,
if you don't mind me saying.

79
00:08:10,239 --> 00:08:13,658
It's the only facility of its kind in the U.S.,
even the world.

80
00:08:13,743 --> 00:08:16,286
We take only the most dangerous,
damaged patients,

81
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:18,329
ones no other hospital can manage.

82
00:08:18,414 --> 00:08:20,331
And it's all due to Dr. Cawley.

83
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:22,333
He's created something
really unique here.

84
00:08:22,418 --> 00:08:26,004
It's a hospital for people our society
normally considers beyond treatment.

85
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:52,572
Top of his class at Johns Hopkins,
then Harvard...

86
00:08:53,991 --> 00:08:55,742
IDs, gentlemen.

87
00:08:59,246 --> 00:09:01,372
Show your badges, gentlemen.

88
00:09:01,457 --> 00:09:05,418
Dr. Cawley's been consulted
numerous times by Scotland Yard,

89
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:07,253
Ml5, the OSS...

90
00:09:07,338 --> 00:09:08,922
Why?

91
00:09:09,006 --> 00:09:10,673
What do you mean?

92
00:09:12,009 --> 00:09:15,261
What do intelligence agencies
want to consult a psychiatrist about?

93
00:09:15,346 --> 00:09:17,639
I guess you'll have to ask him.

94
00:09:27,483 --> 00:09:29,526
- Marshal Daniels.
- Doctor.

95
00:09:29,985 --> 00:09:31,569
Marshal Aule.

96
00:09:32,029 --> 00:09:34,739
Thank you, Deputy Warden.
That will be all.

97
00:09:34,824 --> 00:09:37,492
Yes, sir. Pleasure, gentlemen.

98
00:09:39,161 --> 00:09:40,829
He had a lot to say about you.

99
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:44,124
McPherson's a good man.
He believes in the work we do here.

100
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:46,501
And what would that be, exactly?

101
00:09:46,585 --> 00:09:50,255
A moral fusion between law and order
and clinical care.

102
00:09:50,339 --> 00:09:53,341
Pardon me, Doc.
A what between what and what?

103
00:10:00,307 --> 00:10:03,351
Those paintings are quite accurate.

104
00:10:03,435 --> 00:10:05,311
Used to be the kind of patients
we deal with here

105
00:10:05,396 --> 00:10:08,606
were shackled and left in their own filth.

106
00:10:08,691 --> 00:10:09,983
They were beaten,

107
00:10:10,067 --> 00:10:12,318
as if whipping them bloody
would drive the psychosis out.

108
00:10:12,403 --> 00:10:14,487
We drove screws into their brains,

109
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:18,408
we submerged them in icy water
until they lost consciousness

110
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:20,952
or even drowned.

111
00:10:21,036 --> 00:10:22,996
- And now?
- We treat them.

112
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:25,290
Try to heal, try to cure.

113
00:10:25,374 --> 00:10:27,000
And if that fails,
at least we provide them

114
00:10:27,084 --> 00:10:30,336
with a measure of comfort
in their lives. Calm.

115
00:10:30,421 --> 00:10:33,673
These are all violent offenders, right?

116
00:10:33,757 --> 00:10:36,009
I mean, they've hurt people.

117
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:40,513
- Murdered them in some cases.
- In almost all cases, yes.

118
00:10:40,598 --> 00:10:42,432
Then, personally, Doctor,
I'd have to say,

119
00:10:42,516 --> 00:10:44,893
screw their sense of calm.

120
00:10:46,478 --> 00:10:48,688
It's my job to treat my patients,
not their victims.

121
00:10:48,772 --> 00:10:50,231
I'm not here to judge.

122
00:10:50,316 --> 00:10:52,942
- So this female prisoner...
- Patient.

123
00:10:53,777 --> 00:10:55,695
Excuse me. Patient,

124
00:10:55,779 --> 00:11:00,867
one Rachel Solando,
escaped sometime in the last 24 hours.

125
00:11:00,951 --> 00:11:03,203
Last night between 10:00 and midnight.

126
00:11:03,287 --> 00:11:04,871
Is she considered dangerous?

127
00:11:04,955 --> 00:11:08,583
You could say that.
She killed all three of her children.

128
00:11:09,501 --> 00:11:12,378
She drowned them in the lake
behind her house.

129
00:11:12,463 --> 00:11:15,757
She took them out one by one,
held their heads under till they died,

130
00:11:15,841 --> 00:11:18,718
then she brought them back inside and
arranged them around the kitchen table.

131
00:11:18,802 --> 00:11:22,138
She ate a meal there
before a neighbor dropped by.

132
00:11:24,099 --> 00:11:27,977
- And what about the husband?
- He died on the beaches of Normandy.

133
00:11:28,062 --> 00:11:32,065
She's a war widow. She starved herself
when she first came here.

134
00:11:32,149 --> 00:11:34,984
She insisted the children weren't dead.

135
00:11:44,828 --> 00:11:47,580
Sorry, Doctor. You don't happen
to have an aspirin, do you?

136
00:11:47,665 --> 00:11:49,332
Prone to headaches, Marshal?

137
00:11:49,416 --> 00:11:52,669
Sometimes. But today,
I'm a little more prone to seasickness.

138
00:11:53,462 --> 00:11:54,629
Dehydration.

139
00:11:54,713 --> 00:11:56,339
- You all right, boss?
- Yeah.

140
00:11:56,423 --> 00:11:59,133
In that case, you're quite right.
The simpler the better.

141
00:11:59,218 --> 00:12:00,760
Thanks so much.

142
00:12:01,637 --> 00:12:04,639
Rachel still believes
the children are alive.

143
00:12:05,182 --> 00:12:08,977
She also believes this place is her home
in the Berkshires.

144
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:11,229
You're kidding me.

145
00:12:11,313 --> 00:12:12,563
She's never once in two years

146
00:12:12,648 --> 00:12:14,315
acknowledged that
she's in an institution.

147
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:18,278
She believes we're all deliverymen,
milkmen, postal workers.

148
00:12:18,362 --> 00:12:20,571
To sustain the delusion
that her children never died,

149
00:12:20,656 --> 00:12:22,657
she's created
an elaborate fictional structure,

150
00:12:22,741 --> 00:12:26,119
and she gives us all parts
to play in that fiction.

151
00:12:27,037 --> 00:12:29,122
So have you searched the grounds yet?

152
00:12:29,206 --> 00:12:31,791
The warden and his men
scoured the island.

153
00:12:31,875 --> 00:12:33,376
Not a trace.

154
00:12:33,961 --> 00:12:38,506
And what's more disturbing is we don't
know how she got out of her room.

155
00:12:38,590 --> 00:12:42,385
It was locked from the outside,
and the only window is barred.

156
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:48,683
It's as if she evaporated
straight through the walls.

157
00:12:54,565 --> 00:12:58,401
I brought her right back here
after group therapy, locked her in,

158
00:12:58,485 --> 00:13:01,487
came back for midnight rounds,
she was gone.

159
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:12,498
Seriously, Doctor, how is it possible
that the truth never gets through to her?

160
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:15,501
I mean,
she's in a mental institution, right?

161
00:13:15,586 --> 00:13:17,587
Seems like something you'd notice
from time to time.

162
00:13:17,671 --> 00:13:19,839
How many pairs of shoes
are the patients given?

163
00:13:19,923 --> 00:13:21,299
Two pairs.

164
00:13:21,383 --> 00:13:25,636
Sanity's not a choice, Marshal.
You can't just choose to get over it.

165
00:13:26,221 --> 00:13:29,140
So, she left here barefoot?

166
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:33,019
Come on, Doc, she couldn't get
10 yards in that terrain.

167
00:13:34,396 --> 00:13:35,688
Marshal?

168
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:56,709
This is definitely Rachel's handwriting.

169
00:13:56,794 --> 00:13:59,629
I have no idea
what the law of four is, though.

170
00:13:59,713 --> 00:14:02,548
- It's not a psychiatric term?
- I'm afraid not.

171
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:04,133
"Who is 67?"

172
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:06,469
Fuck if I know.

173
00:14:06,553 --> 00:14:10,390
I have to say that's quite close
to my clinical conclusion.

174
00:14:10,474 --> 00:14:12,392
Think it's just random scribblings?

175
00:14:12,476 --> 00:14:16,229
Oh, no, not at all. Rachel's smart.
Brilliant, in fact.

176
00:14:16,313 --> 00:14:17,730
This paper could be important.

177
00:14:17,815 --> 00:14:20,691
Excuse me, Doctor,
but we're gonna have to hold on to this.

178
00:14:20,776 --> 00:14:22,151
Of course.

179
00:14:24,071 --> 00:14:26,948
And you say
she had to come through here?

180
00:14:27,032 --> 00:14:31,285
After lights out,
the orderlies play cards in here.

181
00:14:31,370 --> 00:14:34,705
Last night, there were seven men
sitting at the base of those stairs

182
00:14:34,790 --> 00:14:36,249
playing stud poker.

183
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:39,377
Yet somehow,
Rachel managed to slip past them.

184
00:14:40,087 --> 00:14:41,087
Why?

185
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:43,798
How? She turns invisible?

186
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:46,759
Doctor, we're gonna need access
to the personnel files

187
00:14:46,844 --> 00:14:47,885
of all the medical staff.

188
00:14:47,970 --> 00:14:50,763
The nurses, the guards, the orderlies,
anyone who was working then.

189
00:14:50,848 --> 00:14:53,641
We'll take your request
under consideration.

190
00:14:53,725 --> 00:14:56,352
This is not a request, Doctor.

191
00:14:56,437 --> 00:14:58,938
This is a federal facility,
and a dangerous prisoner...

192
00:14:59,022 --> 00:15:01,232
- Patient.
...patient

193
00:15:01,316 --> 00:15:03,609
has escaped. Now, you will comply or...

194
00:15:03,694 --> 00:15:06,028
All I can say is I'll see what I can do.

195
00:15:06,113 --> 00:15:08,948
Doctor, we're gonna need
to speak with the staff.

196
00:15:09,032 --> 00:15:11,075
Do you understand?

197
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,369
I'll assemble them in the common room
after dinner.

198
00:15:14,496 --> 00:15:15,746
If you have any further questions,

199
00:15:15,831 --> 00:15:19,125
feel free to join the deputy warden
in the search.

200
00:15:31,555 --> 00:15:34,891
It's 11 miles to the nearest land
and the water's freezing.

201
00:15:34,975 --> 00:15:38,019
Current was strong last night,
tide pushing in.

202
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:39,687
She'd have drowned
or been crushed on the rocks,

203
00:15:39,771 --> 00:15:42,940
and her body would have
washed back up on shore.

204
00:15:45,903 --> 00:15:49,155
What about those caves down there?
Have you checked them?

205
00:15:49,239 --> 00:15:51,616
No way she could get there.

206
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:54,494
The bases of those cliffs
are covered in poison ivy,

207
00:15:54,578 --> 00:15:58,623
live oak, sumac, a thousand plants
with thorns as big as my dick.

208
00:15:59,416 --> 00:16:02,585
You said yourself, Marshal,
she's got no shoes.

209
00:16:07,883 --> 00:16:10,593
All right, let's check the other side.

210
00:16:15,974 --> 00:16:18,935
- What's that tower?
- It's an old lighthouse.

211
00:16:19,603 --> 00:16:22,396
The guards already searched inside it.

212
00:16:24,316 --> 00:16:26,526
What's in there? More patients?

213
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,736
Sewage treatment facility.

214
00:16:29,196 --> 00:16:33,115
It's getting dark soon.
I'm calling this off for tonight.

215
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,742
Let's go, boys!

216
00:16:38,622 --> 00:16:40,540
You were on watch on the landing, huh?

217
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:44,043
Yeah. Couldn't nobody get in or out
of their room on that corridor

218
00:16:44,127 --> 00:16:45,878
without me seeing.

219
00:16:45,963 --> 00:16:50,675
Okay, Rachel Solando, who else does
she have to pass to get down here?

220
00:16:56,890 --> 00:16:59,559
Me. Glen Miga.

221
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:02,395
Sir, I didn't see nothing.

222
00:17:02,813 --> 00:17:04,814
And you were at your post all night?

223
00:17:04,898 --> 00:17:07,233
Yeah, but I didn't see a thing.

224
00:17:09,236 --> 00:17:13,281
Glen.

225
00:17:16,118 --> 00:17:17,868
Tell me the truth.

226
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:20,288
I...

227
00:17:22,332 --> 00:17:24,584
I maybe went to the bathroom.

228
00:17:25,085 --> 00:17:27,753
What? You breached protocol. Christ...

229
00:17:27,838 --> 00:17:30,172
I wasn't gone more than a minute.

230
00:17:30,257 --> 00:17:33,259
All right, look. Let's back up here.
Let's all just back up.

231
00:17:33,343 --> 00:17:36,762
Miss Solando was put in her room
for lights out.

232
00:17:36,847 --> 00:17:40,266
Does anyone here know
what she did before that?

233
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:41,559
Anyone?

234
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:45,479
Come on, anyone,
anyone, anyone, anyone.

235
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:48,065
She was in a group therapy session.

236
00:17:49,526 --> 00:17:51,444
Anything unusual occur?

237
00:17:52,029 --> 00:17:53,738
Define "unusual."

238
00:17:54,239 --> 00:17:55,281
Excuse me?

239
00:17:55,365 --> 00:17:59,744
This is a mental institution, Marshal,
for the criminally insane.

240
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:02,371
Usual isn't a big part of our day.

241
00:18:03,832 --> 00:18:05,458
I will rephrase.

242
00:18:05,542 --> 00:18:09,462
Did anything happen last night
during group therapy that was more,

243
00:18:09,546 --> 00:18:12,048
let's say, I don't know,
memorable than...

244
00:18:12,132 --> 00:18:13,883
- Normal?
- Exactly.

245
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:16,344
No. Sorry.

246
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:20,014
Did Miss Solando say anything
during group therapy?

247
00:18:20,891 --> 00:18:23,184
