01:18:15,482 --> 01:18:17,316
Because climbing down there
when it's dark

991
01:18:17,400 --> 01:18:20,569
is a thin step short of suicide,
that's why.

992
01:18:20,654 --> 01:18:24,073
Okay, maybe you better sit
this one out then.

993
01:18:25,659 --> 01:18:28,953
You brought me into this, boss,
and now we're trapped here

994
01:18:29,037 --> 01:18:32,706
on this rock, on this island,
with no one to rely on but each other,

995
01:18:32,791 --> 01:18:34,750
and now you're acting like...

996
01:18:34,834 --> 01:18:37,836
Like what? Like what? How am I acting?

997
01:18:42,676 --> 01:18:46,136
What the hell happened back there
in those cells, Ted?

998
01:18:50,850 --> 01:18:54,103
What do you think the weather's like
in Portland, Chuck?

999
01:18:54,187 --> 01:18:55,854
I'm from Seattle.

1000
01:18:58,483 --> 01:18:59,733
Seattle.

1001
01:19:02,946 --> 01:19:05,698
I'm going on alone.

1002
01:19:08,618 --> 01:19:11,495
- I'm going with you, boss.
- I said alone.

1003
01:19:13,206 --> 01:19:14,331
Fine.

1004
01:19:40,984 --> 01:19:42,234
Damn it!

1005
01:19:43,236 --> 01:19:44,528
Damn it.

1006
01:19:49,743 --> 01:19:52,619
I knew it wouldn't take long,
but I couldn't get to it.

1007
01:19:52,704 --> 01:19:54,246
The tide was up.

1008
01:20:02,505 --> 01:20:07,343
Chuck!

1009
01:21:08,905 --> 01:21:10,155
Come on!

1010
01:21:45,525 --> 01:21:46,692
Chuck!

1011
01:21:47,277 --> 01:21:49,194
Where are you, Chuck?

1012
01:22:13,845 --> 01:22:17,931
Chuck!

1013
01:23:02,435 --> 01:23:03,810
Who are you?

1014
01:23:05,939 --> 01:23:08,774
I'm Teddy Daniels. I'm a cop.

1015
01:23:10,151 --> 01:23:11,860
You're the marshal.

1016
01:23:12,904 --> 01:23:14,321
That's right.

1017
01:23:16,658 --> 01:23:20,536
Would you mind taking your hand
from behind your back, please?

1018
01:23:20,620 --> 01:23:22,454
Why? Why?

1019
01:23:23,957 --> 01:23:26,959
I wanna make sure that
what you're holding won't hurt me.

1020
01:23:34,634 --> 01:23:36,343
I'm gonna keep this

1021
01:23:37,845 --> 01:23:39,346
if you don't mind.

1022
01:23:40,181 --> 01:23:41,598
Fine by me.

1023
01:23:50,650 --> 01:23:51,984
You're...

1024
01:23:53,403 --> 01:23:55,237
You're Rachel Solando.

1025
01:23:56,823 --> 01:23:58,240
The real one.

1026
01:24:02,245 --> 01:24:03,870
Did you kill your children?

1027
01:24:05,665 --> 01:24:07,499
I never had children.

1028
01:24:08,167 --> 01:24:09,960
I was never married.

1029
01:24:11,504 --> 01:24:15,048
And before I was a patient at Ashecliffe,
I worked here.

1030
01:24:15,675 --> 01:24:18,260
You... You were a nurse?

1031
01:24:20,597 --> 01:24:22,556
I was a doctor, Marshal.

1032
01:24:25,977 --> 01:24:27,686
You think I'm crazy.

1033
01:24:28,062 --> 01:24:31,398
- No. No, no, I never...
- And if I say I'm not crazy?

1034
01:24:32,609 --> 01:24:35,027
Well, that hardly helps, does it?

1035
01:24:35,862 --> 01:24:38,363
That's the Kafkaesque genius of it.

1036
01:24:41,659 --> 01:24:43,952
People tell the world you're crazy,

1037
01:24:44,037 --> 01:24:47,956
and all your protests to the contrary
just confirm what they're saying.

1038
01:24:48,541 --> 01:24:51,710
I'm not following you. I'm sorry.

1039
01:24:52,337 --> 01:24:54,296
Once you're declared insane,

1040
01:24:54,380 --> 01:24:57,883
then anything you do
is called part of that insanity.

1041
01:24:57,967 --> 01:25:03,555
Reasonable protests are denial.
Valid fears, paranoia.

1042
01:25:03,640 --> 01:25:07,726
Survival instincts
are defense mechanisms.

1043
01:25:08,019 --> 01:25:11,730
You're smarter than you look, Marshal.
That's probably not a good thing.

1044
01:25:12,607 --> 01:25:14,066
Tell me something.

1045
01:25:14,150 --> 01:25:15,275
Yeah.

1046
01:25:16,444 --> 01:25:18,236
What happened to you?

1047
01:25:19,072 --> 01:25:22,491
I started asking about these
large shipments of sodium amytal

1048
01:25:22,575 --> 01:25:24,326
and opium-based hallucinogens.

1049
01:25:24,410 --> 01:25:26,119
Psychotropic drugs.

1050
01:25:27,497 --> 01:25:29,873
I asked about the surgeries, too.

1051
01:25:31,918 --> 01:25:34,086
You ever heard of
a transorbital lobotomy?

1052
01:25:35,630 --> 01:25:38,340
They zap the patient with electroshock,

1053
01:25:38,424 --> 01:25:41,259
then go through the eye with an ice pick,

1054
01:25:43,429 --> 01:25:45,514
pull out some nerve fibers.

1055
01:25:47,934 --> 01:25:50,394
Makes the patients much more obedient.

1056
01:25:50,478 --> 01:25:51,812
Tractable.

1057
01:25:53,272 --> 01:25:54,773
It's barbaric,

1058
01:25:55,775 --> 01:25:57,275
unconscionable.

1059
01:25:58,277 --> 01:26:02,030
Do you know how pain
enters the body, Marshal? Do you?

1060
01:26:03,282 --> 01:26:04,741
Depends on where you're hurt?

1061
01:26:04,826 --> 01:26:09,996
No, it has nothing to do with the flesh.
The brain controls pain.

1062
01:26:10,623 --> 01:26:15,001
The brain controls fear, empathy, sleep,
hunger, anger. Everything.

1063
01:26:17,338 --> 01:26:19,131
What if you could control it?

1064
01:26:19,632 --> 01:26:21,091
You mean the brain?

1065
01:26:21,175 --> 01:26:27,973
Recreate a man so he doesn't feel
pain or love or sympathy.

1066
01:26:29,434 --> 01:26:30,892
A man who can't be interrogated,

1067
01:26:30,977 --> 01:26:33,687
because he has no memories
to confess.

1068
01:26:36,274 --> 01:26:39,943
You can never take away
all a man's memories. Never.

1069
01:26:40,027 --> 01:26:44,156
Marshal, the North Koreans
used American POWs

1070
01:26:44,240 --> 01:26:45,907
during their brainwashing experiments.

1071
01:26:45,992 --> 01:26:49,411
They turned soldiers into traitors.
That's what they're doing here.

1072
01:26:49,495 --> 01:26:51,580
They're creating ghosts
to go out in the world

1073
01:26:51,664 --> 01:26:54,916
and do things sane men...
Sane men never would.

1074
01:26:55,001 --> 01:26:58,336
To have that kind of ability,
that kind of knowledge,

1075
01:26:58,421 --> 01:27:00,672
- that would take years.
- Years. Years of research.

1076
01:27:01,174 --> 01:27:03,884
Hundreds of patients to experiment on.

1077
01:27:05,136 --> 01:27:07,554
Fifty years from now,
people will look back

1078
01:27:07,638 --> 01:27:11,016
and say, here, this place,
is where it all began.

1079
01:27:11,726 --> 01:27:16,521
The Nazis used the Jews, Soviets used
prisoners in their own Gulags,

1080
01:27:17,356 --> 01:27:20,817
and we tested patients
on Shutter Island.

1081
01:27:22,487 --> 01:27:24,154
No, they won't.

1082
01:27:25,114 --> 01:27:26,114
No.

1083
01:27:28,576 --> 01:27:30,702
You do understand

1084
01:27:33,247 --> 01:27:35,540
that they can't let you leave.

1085
01:27:35,833 --> 01:27:39,169
I am a federal marshal.
They can't stop me.

1086
01:27:40,546 --> 01:27:45,634
I was an esteemed psychiatrist
from a respected family.

1087
01:27:47,720 --> 01:27:49,346
Didn't matter.

1088
01:27:52,058 --> 01:27:53,642
Let me ask you.

1089
01:27:53,726 --> 01:27:56,102
Any past traumas in your life?

1090
01:27:57,480 --> 01:27:58,730
Yes.

1091
01:27:59,899 --> 01:28:01,983
But why would that matter?

1092
01:28:02,068 --> 01:28:04,361
Because they're gonna point
to some event in your past

1093
01:28:04,445 --> 01:28:06,947
and say it's the reason
you lost your sanity.

1094
01:28:07,031 --> 01:28:12,410
So that when they commit you here,
your friends and colleagues will say,

1095
01:28:12,495 --> 01:28:14,412
"Of course he cracked.

1096
01:28:15,414 --> 01:28:16,665
"Who wouldn't after what
he'd been through?"

1097
01:28:16,749 --> 01:28:19,251
They can say that about anyone,
anyone at all.

1098
01:28:19,335 --> 01:28:22,295
The point is
they're gonna say it about you.

1099
01:28:25,550 --> 01:28:27,175
How's your head?

1100
01:28:27,260 --> 01:28:29,344
My head?

1101
01:28:29,428 --> 01:28:32,848
Any funny dreams lately?
Trouble sleeping?

1102
01:28:35,059 --> 01:28:39,396
- Headaches?
- I am prone to migraines, yes.

1103
01:28:39,480 --> 01:28:40,772
Jesus.

1104
01:28:43,067 --> 01:28:46,570
You haven't taken any pills, have you?
I mean, even aspirin?

1105
01:28:46,654 --> 01:28:48,822
- The aspirin?
- Jesus.

1106
01:28:49,490 --> 01:28:53,201
And you ate the food in the cafeteria
and drank the coffee they gave you?

1107
01:28:53,286 --> 01:28:56,663
You tell me, at least, that you've
been smoking your own cigarettes.

1108
01:28:58,457 --> 01:29:01,751
No.

1109
01:29:02,837 --> 01:29:04,212
No, I haven't.

1110
01:29:04,297 --> 01:29:07,048
It takes 36 to 48 hours
for neuroleptic narcotics

1111
01:29:07,133 --> 01:29:09,718
to reach workable levels
in the bloodstream.

1112
01:29:11,512 --> 01:29:13,346
Palsy comes first,

1113
01:29:14,265 --> 01:29:17,726
first the fingertips,
then eventually the whole hand.

1114
01:29:18,644 --> 01:29:22,814
Seen any walking nightmares
lately, Marshal?

1115
01:29:25,318 --> 01:29:28,278
Tell me what goes on in that lighthouse.

1116
01:29:29,155 --> 01:29:30,488
Tell me.

1117
01:29:31,657 --> 01:29:33,283
Brain surgery.

1118
01:29:33,951 --> 01:29:38,413
The let's-open-the-skull-and-see-
what-happens-if-we-pull-on-this kind.

1119
01:29:38,956 --> 01:29:41,833
The learned-it-from-the-Nazis kind.

1120
01:29:43,920 --> 01:29:46,379
That's where they create the ghosts.

1121
01:29:47,798 --> 01:29:51,676
Who knows about this?
On the island, I mean. Who?

1122
01:29:54,013 --> 01:29:55,263
Everyone.

1123
01:29:55,348 --> 01:29:59,059
Come on. The nurses? The orderlies?

1124
01:29:59,644 --> 01:30:02,938
- They couldn't possibly know...
- Everyone.

1125
01:30:21,874 --> 01:30:23,416
You can't stay here.

1126
01:30:24,043 --> 01:30:25,335
They think I'm dead, that I drowned.

1127
01:30:25,419 --> 01:30:28,421
I'm afraid if they come looking for you,
they might find me.

1128
01:30:28,506 --> 01:30:30,882
I'm sorry, but you have to go.

1129
01:30:37,515 --> 01:30:39,140
I'm gonna come back for you.

1130
01:30:39,225 --> 01:30:42,185
I won't be here. I move during the day.
New places every night.

1131
01:30:42,269 --> 01:30:44,604
But I could come get you,
get you off this island.

1132
01:30:44,689 --> 01:30:47,399
Haven't you heard a word I've said?

1133
01:30:47,483 --> 01:30:51,611
The only way off the island is the ferry,
and they control it.

1134
01:30:51,696 --> 01:30:53,738
You'll never leave here.

1135
01:31:03,082 --> 01:31:04,874
I had a friend.

1136
01:31:04,959 --> 01:31:08,503
I was with him yesterday,
but we got separated.

1137
01:31:08,587 --> 01:31:10,255
Have you seen him?

1138
01:31:11,424 --> 01:31:12,757
Marshal,

1139
01:31:14,301 --> 01:31:16,428
you have no friends.

1140
01:31:48,753 --> 01:31:50,295
There you are.

1141
01:31:53,132 --> 01:31:55,800
We were wondering
when you'd show up.

1142
01:31:57,428 --> 01:31:58,970
Have a seat.

1143
01:31:59,430 --> 01:32:00,722
Come on.

1144
01:32:11,400 --> 01:32:14,027
Taking a leisurely stroll, were we?

1145
01:32:15,112 --> 01:32:18,156
I was just looking around.

1146
01:32:21,118 --> 01:32:23,536
Did you enjoy God's latest gift?

1147
01:32:25,164 --> 01:32:26,498
- What?
- God's gift.

1148
01:32:28,667 --> 01:32:30,001
The violence.

1149
01:32:32,838 --> 01:32:37,217
When I came downstairs in my home
and I saw that tree in my living room,

1150
01:32:37,301 --> 01:32:41,137
it reached out for me like a divine hand.

1151
01:32:43,349 --> 01:32:45,183
God loves violence.

1152
01:32:47,853 --> 01:32:50,688
- I hadn't noticed.
- Sure you have.

1153
01:32:51,857 --> 01:32:56,986
Why else would there be so much of it?
It's in us. It's what we are.

1154
01:32:59,031 --> 01:33:01,366
We wage war, we burn sacrifices,

1155
01:33:01,450 --> 01:33:03,993
and pillage and plunder
and tear at the flesh of our brothers.

1156
01:33:04,078 --> 01:33:07,997
And why? Because God gave us
violence to wage in his honor.

1157
01:33:11,210 --> 01:33:13,628
I thought God gave us moral order.

1158
01:33:13,712 --> 01:33:16,714
There's no moral order
as pure as this storm.

1159
01:33:17,341 --> 01:33:19,634
There's no moral order at all.

1160
01:33:19,927 --> 01:33:23,471
There's just this,
can my violence conquer yours?

1161
01:33:29,061 --> 01:33:31,479
- I'm not violent.
- Yes, you are.

1162
01:33:32,606 --> 01:33:35,024
You're as violent as they come.

1163
01:33:35,734 --> 01:33:39,320
I know this
because I'm as violent as they come.

1164
01:33:39,405 --> 01:33:41,573
If the constraints of society were lifted,

1165
01:33:41,657 --> 01:33:44,325
and I was all that stood
between you and a meal,

1166
01:33:44,410 --> 01:33:48,204
you would crack my skull with a rock
and eat my meaty parts.

1167
01:33:49,748 --> 01:33:51,332
Wouldn't you?

1168
01:33:54,086 --> 01:33:56,546
Cawley thinks you're harmless,
that you can be controlled,

1169
01:33:56,630 --> 01:33:58,506
but I know different.

1170
01:33:59,133 --> 01:34:00,884
- You don't know me.
- Oh, but I do.

1171
01:34:00,968 --> 01:34:04,137
- No, you don't. You don't know me at all.
- Oh, I know you.

1172
01:34:04,221 --> 01:34:06,931
We've known each other for centuries.

1173
01:34:16,275 --> 01:34:19,194
If I was to sink my teeth
into your eye right now,

1174
01:34:19,278 --> 01:34:22,614
would you be able to stop me
before I blinded you?

1175
01:34:26,744 --> 01:34:28,369
Give it a try.

1176
01:34:29,914 --> 01:34:31,623
That's the spirit.

1177
01:35:06,367 --> 01:35:08,993
Don't worry, because we're going
to get you back to your room.

1178
01:35:10,621 --> 01:35:12,288
- Not really.
- Something I've seen.

1179
01:35:12,373 --> 01:35:13,623
Okay.

1180
01:35:18,837 --> 01:35:20,588
Where have you been?

1181
01:35:20,673 --> 01:35:23,424
Oh, just wandering.
Just looking at your island.

1182
01:35:23,509 --> 01:35:27,178
Oh, I forgot you're leaving
now that Rachel's been found.

1183
01:35:28,013 --> 01:35:29,430
- Stop looking at him.
- For sure. Yeah.

1184
01:35:29,515 --> 01:35:32,767
Stop looking at him. Stop looking at him.

1185
01:35:32,851 --> 01:35:34,852
- Big meeting?
- Oh, yes.

1186
01:35:34,937 --> 01:35:36,604
- It's okay. I'm...
- I don't like that.

1187
01:35:36,689 --> 01:35:38,690
Apparently there was
an unidentified man

1188
01:35:38,774 --> 01:35:40,066
in Ward C yesterday.

1189
01:35:40,150 --> 01:35:43,528
He subdued a highly dangerous patient
quite handily.

1190
01:35:44,113 --> 01:35:45,113
Is that so?

1191
01:35:45,197 --> 01:35:47,657
It seems he had a long conversation
with a paranoid schizophrenic,

1192
01:35:47,741 --> 01:35:48,950
George Noyce.

1193
01:35:49,034 --> 01:35:51,828
Well, I don't remember
what I'm supposed to remember.

1194
01:35:51,912 --> 01:35:53,621
We're gated down. We're fine.

1195
01:35:53,706 --> 01:35:57,750
This Noyce, you said
his name was, he's delusional?

1196
01:35:57,835 --> 01:36:00,545
Extremely. He can be quite upsetting.

1197
01:36:00,629 --> 01:36:02,338
As a matter of fact, two weeks ago,

1198
01:36:02,423 --> 01:36:06,884
a patient got so wound up by one
of Noyce's stories that he beat him up.

1199
01:36:08,137 --> 01:36:09,554
Cigarette?

1200
01:36:11,348 --> 01:36:13,141
No, thanks. I quit.

1201
01:36:14,226 --> 01:36:18,271
- So you're taking the ferry?
- Yes, absolutely.

1202
01:36:18,355 --> 01:36:21,816
I think we've gotten
all we came here for, so...

1203
01:36:21,900 --> 01:36:23,234
"We," Marshal?

1204
01:36:25,237 --> 01:36:28,823
Speaking of which,
have you seen him, Doctor?

1205
01:36:28,907 --> 01:36:30,074
Who?

1206
01:36:30,909 --> 01:36:32,618
My partner, Chuck.

1207
01:36:34,955 --> 01:36:37,790
You don't have a partner, Marshal.
You came here alone.

1208
01:36:40,252 --> 01:36:42,420
You know, I've built
something valuable here,

1209
01:36:42,504 --> 01:36:45,673
and valuable things have a way of
being misunderstood in their own time.

1210
01:36:45,758 --> 01:36:47,842
Everyone wants a quick fix.
They always have.

1211
01:36:47,926 --> 01:36:51,512
I'm trying to do something that people,
yourself included, don't understand.

1212
01:36:51,597 --> 01:36:54,557
And I'm not going to give up
without a fight.

1213
01:36:56,393 --> 01:36:58,019
I can see that.

1214
01:37:02,107 --> 01:37:04,734
So, tell me again about your partner.

1215
01:37:06,445 --> 01:37:08,071
What partner?

1216
01:37:10,824 --> 01:37:11,908
It's fine.

1217
01:38:00,249 --> 01:38:04,043
She made a mess. I cleaned it up.
She made a mess again.

1218
01:38:13,345 --> 01:38:14,720
Marshal,

1219
01:38:16,098 --> 01:38:17,723
going somewhere?

1220
01:38:18,016 --> 01:38:21,185
I'm just heading out to the ferry, so...

1221
01:38:21,687 --> 01:38:25,231
Oh, well, I'm afraid it's the other way.

1222
01:38:28,193 --> 01:38:32,864
If you'll wait a moment, I'll find you
someone who can take you to the dock.

1223
01:38:37,536 --> 01:38:41,372
- What's this, Doctor? What's this?
- It's just a sedative.

1224
01:38:41,457 --> 01:38:44,625
- A precaution.
- A precaution.

1225
01:38:47,546 --> 01:38:51,632
What are you going to do?
Kill me? Marshal.

1226
01:38:52,009 --> 01:38:53,551
You think you deserve it?

1227
01:38:53,635 --> 01:38:56,429
For what? Provoking you?

1228
01:38:57,222 --> 01:39:00,057
Well, forgive me.
What doesn't provoke you?

1229
01:39:00,601 --> 01:39:03,728
- Remarks? Words?
- Nazis?

1230
01:39:04,188 --> 01:39:08,232
Well, that, too.
And, of course, memories, dreams.

1231
01:39:09,318 --> 01:39:13,571
Did you know that the word "trauma"
comes from the Greek for "wound"?

1232
01:39:14,239 --> 01:39:16,991
And what is the German word
for "dream"?

1233
01:39:20,621 --> 01:39:23,581
Wounds can create monsters,
and you...

1234
01:39:24,249 --> 01:39:26,626
You are wounded, Marshal.

1235
01:39:27,669 --> 01:39:30,838
And wouldn't you agree,
when you see a monster,

1236
01:39:31,548 --> 01:39:33,299
you must stop it?

1237
01:39:33,884 --> 01:39:35,092
Yeah.

1238
01:39:36,261 --> 01:39:38,095
- I agree.
- Yes.

1239
01:39:38,931 --> 01:39:40,014
Yeah.

1240
01:39:57,241 --> 01:39:59,492
I told him that we'd take
about an hour to do it.

1241
01:39:59,576 --> 01:40:02,662
Yeah. Did they say
we're going to do the first floor?

1242
01:40:02,746 --> 01:40:03,996
How long you been on the clock?

1243
01:40:04,081 --> 01:40:07,792
- I've been on for 18 hours straight.
- Nice paycheck.

1244
01:40:24,935 --> 01:40:27,019
What are you doing, baby?

1245
01:40:31,817 --> 01:40:34,318
- You gotta get to the ferry.
- No.

1246
01:40:35,070 --> 01:40:36,362
No, no.

1247
01:40:37,573 --> 01:40:38,739
Yeah.

1248
01:40:39,866 --> 01:40:44,745
If the world thinks that Chuck is dead,
then he's perfect for their experiments.

1249
01:40:45,831 --> 01:40:48,082
There's only one place they'd take him.

1250
01:40:50,711 --> 01:40:52,336
You go there and you'll die.

1251
01:40:52,421 --> 01:40:54,088
He's my partner. If they are hurting him,

1252
01:40:54,172 --> 01:40:57,341
if they're holding him against his will,
I've gotta bring him out.

1253
01:40:57,426 --> 01:40:59,468
I can't lose anyone else.

1254
01:40:59,553 --> 01:41:00,803
Don't go, Teddy, please.

1255
01:41:00,887 --> 01:41:04,307
- Please, don't do this. Don't go.
- I'm sorry, honey.

1256
01:41:07,894 --> 01:41:09,687
I'm sorry, honey.

1257
01:41:10,772 --> 01:41:13,816
I love this thing
because you gave it to me,

1258
01:41:16,194 --> 01:41:18,029
but the truth is

1259
01:41:19,698 --> 01:41:21,866
it is one fucking ugly tie.

1260
01:42:02,074 --> 01:42:03,240
No.

1261
01:43:25,157 --> 01:43:26,532
Don't move. Stay where you are.

1262
01:43:28,535 --> 01:43:29,952
Are you gonna kill me?

1263
01:43:31,621 --> 01:43:34,165
No, I'm not gonna kill you.

1264
01:45:26,778 --> 01:45:28,654
Why are you all wet, baby?

1265
01:45:30,866 --> 01:45:34,118
- What did you say?
- You know exactly what I said.

1266
01:45:47,215 --> 01:45:49,466
The rifle's empty, by the way.

1267
01:45:55,974 --> 01:45:57,474
Have a seat.

1268
01:46:03,982 --> 01:46:06,400
For God's sake, dry off.
You'll catch cold.

1269
01:46:08,028 --> 01:46:09,153
All right.

1270
01:46:12,699 --> 01:46:14,617
How badly did you hurt the guard?

1271
01:46:16,328 --> 01:46:19,330
I don't know what you're talking about.

1272
01:46:22,500 --> 01:46:24,418
Yes, he's here.

1273
01:46:24,502 --> 01:46:28,505
Have Dr. Sheehan take a look at
your man before you send him up.

1274
01:46:28,590 --> 01:46:33,302
So Dr. Sheehan came in
on the ferry this morning, huh?

1275
01:46:34,262 --> 01:46:35,763
Not exactly.

1276
01:46:36,806 --> 01:46:39,850
You blew up my car.
I really loved that car.

1277
01:46:40,769 --> 01:46:42,853
Sorry to hear about that.

1278
01:46:46,149 --> 01:46:48,525
Tremors are getting pretty bad.

1279
01:46:49,152 --> 01:46:51,570
How are the hallucinations?

1280
01:46:51,655 --> 01:46:53,948
Get out of here, Teddy.

1281
01:46:54,032 --> 01:46:55,824
This place is gonna be the end of you.

1282
01:46:59,579 --> 01:47:00,704
Not bad.

1283
01:47:00,789 --> 01:47:03,374
- They'll get worse.
- I know.

1284
01:47:04,250 --> 01:47:08,545
Dr. Solando,
she told me about the neuroleptics.

1285
01:47:09,089 --> 01:47:11,548
Did she, now? And when was this?

1286
01:47:11,633 --> 01:47:16,428
I found her, Doctor,
in a cave out by the cliffs.

1287
01:47:16,513 --> 01:47:17,888
But you'll never get to her.

1288
01:47:17,973 --> 01:47:21,392
I don't doubt it,
considering she's not real.

1289
01:47:23,603 --> 01:47:26,730
Your delusions are more severe
than I thought.

1290
01:47:27,941 --> 01:47:30,109
You're not on neuroleptics.

1291
01:47:30,568 --> 01:47:32,444
You're not on anything,
as a matter of fact.

1292
01:47:32,529 --> 01:47:35,155
Then what the fuck is this?
What the fuck is this?

1293
01:47:35,240 --> 01:47:36,240
Withdrawal.

1294
01:47:37,242 --> 01:47:39,201
Withdrawal? From what?

1295
01:47:39,285 --> 01:47:41,620
I haven't had a goddamn drink
since I've been on this island.

1296
01:47:41,705 --> 01:47:43,330
Chlorpromazine.

1297
01:47:44,165 --> 01:47:47,835
I'm not a fan of pharmacology,
but I have to say, in your case...

1298
01:47:47,919 --> 01:47:51,171
- Chloraproma-what?
- Chlorpromazine.

1299
01:47:51,256 --> 01:47:55,259
The same thing we've been giving you
for the past 24 months.

1300
01:47:56,553 --> 01:47:58,679
So for the past two years, you...

1301
01:47:58,763 --> 01:48:02,057
You've had somebody slipping me drugs
in Boston. Is that it?

1302
01:48:02,142 --> 01:48:03,600
Not Boston.

1303
01:48:04,102 --> 01:48:05,269
Here.

1304
01:48:06,062 --> 01:48:10,024
You've been here for two years.
A patient of this institution.

1305
01:48:13,778 --> 01:48:17,531
After everything I've seen here, Doctor,

1306
01:48:17,615 --> 01:48:21,035
you really think you're gonna
convince me I'm crazy?

1307
01:48:21,119 --> 01:48:23,078
Do you know the kind of people
that I deal with every day?

1308
01:48:23,163 --> 01:48:25,039
I'm a U.S. Marshal, for God's sakes.

1309
01:48:25,123 --> 01:48:26,999
You were a U.S. Marshal.

1310
01:48:27,083 --> 01:48:30,878
Here's a copy of the intake form
you broke into Ward C for.

1311
01:48:30,962 --> 01:48:32,337
Proof of the 67th patient.

1312
01:48:32,422 --> 01:48:33,589
If you'd gotten it to the mainland,

1313
01:48:33,673 --> 01:48:35,466
you could have
blown the lid off this place.

1314
01:48:35,550 --> 01:48:36,675
Wait. Where did... Where did you...

1315
01:48:36,760 --> 01:48:38,552
Yet somehow,
you couldn't find time to look at it.

1316
01:48:38,636 --> 01:48:40,345
Well, read it now.

1317
01:48:40,805 --> 01:48:42,181
Go ahead.

1318
01:48:45,977 --> 01:48:49,813
"Patient is highly intelligent, highly
delusional decorated Army veteran.

1319
01:48:49,898 --> 01:48:53,650
"Present for the liberation of Dachau.

1320
01:48:53,735 --> 01:48:56,361
"Former U.S. Marshal.
Known proclivity for violence.

1321
01:48:56,446 --> 01:48:59,698
"Shows no remorse for his crime
because he denies the crime ever...

1322
01:48:59,783 --> 01:49:00,824
"Ever took place.

1323
01:49:00,909 --> 01:49:02,785
"Highly developed
and fantastical narratives,

1324
01:49:02,869 --> 01:49:05,245
"which preclude facing
the truth of his actions."

1325
01:49:05,330 --> 01:49:06,413
I've had enough of this bullshit!

1326
01:49:06,498 --> 01:49:10,375
Where's my partner? Where's Chuck?
Where is he?

1327
01:49:10,460 --> 01:49:12,169
Let's try this another way.

1328
01:49:12,253 --> 01:49:14,797
Your wife's maiden name was Chanal,
am I correct?

1329
01:49:14,881 --> 01:49:16,298
Don't you even talk about her.
Don't you...

1330
01:49:16,382 --> 01:49:18,258
I'm afraid I have to.

1331
01:49:20,345 --> 01:49:24,556
Notice anything these four names
have in common? It's your rule of four.

1332
01:49:24,641 --> 01:49:25,766
Andrew, what do you see?

1333
01:49:25,850 --> 01:49:28,852
If you've done anything to my partner,
Doctor, that is a violation of...

1334
01:49:28,937 --> 01:49:31,355
Focus, Andrew! What do you see?

1335
01:49:32,357 --> 01:49:34,858
The names have the same letters.

1336
01:49:35,735 --> 01:49:39,154
Edward Daniels has exactly
the same 13 letters as Andrew Laeddis.

1337
01:49:39,239 --> 01:49:41,448
The same as Rachel Solando
and Dolores Chanal.

1338
01:49:41,533 --> 01:49:43,617
The names are anagrams
for each other.

1339
01:49:43,701 --> 01:49:46,286
Your tactics,
they're not gonna work on me.

1340
01:49:46,371 --> 01:49:49,164
You came here for the truth. Here it is.

1341
01:49:49,249 --> 01:49:51,250
Your name is Andrew Laeddis.

1342
01:49:51,334 --> 01:49:54,878
The 67th patient at Ashecliffe
is you, Andrew.

1343
01:49:56,714 --> 01:49:57,673
Bullshit.

1344
01:49:57,757 --> 01:49:59,967
You were committed here by court order
24 months ago.

1345
01:50:00,051 --> 01:50:03,387
Your crime is terrible,
one you can't forgive yourself for,

1346
01:50:03,471 --> 01:50:05,848
so you invented another self.

1347
01:50:08,017 --> 01:50:09,434
All right.

1348
01:50:09,936 --> 01:50:12,604
Let's get down to the facts, all right?

1349
01:50:12,689 --> 01:50:15,566
You've created a story
in which you're not a murderer.

1350
01:50:15,650 --> 01:50:17,693
You're a hero, still a U.S. Marshal,

1351
01:50:17,777 --> 01:50:19,695
only here at Ashecliffe
because of a case,

1352
01:50:19,779 --> 01:50:23,115
and you've uncovered a conspiracy
so that anything we tell you

1353
01:50:23,199 --> 01:50:27,035
about who you are, what you've done,
you can dismiss as lies, Andrew.

1354
01:50:27,120 --> 01:50:28,412
My name is Edward Daniels.

1355
01:50:28,496 --> 01:50:32,749
I've been hearing this fantasy for
two years now. I know every detail.

1356
01:50:32,834 --> 01:50:34,793
Patient 67, the storm,

1357
01:50:34,878 --> 01:50:38,088
Rachel Solando, your missing partner,
the dreams you have every night.

1358
01:50:38,173 --> 01:50:40,591
You were at Dachau,
but you may not have killed any guards.

1359
01:50:44,637 --> 01:50:48,307
I wish I could let you just live
in your fantasy world.

1360
01:50:48,391 --> 01:50:49,850
I really do.

1361
01:50:50,727 --> 01:50:52,936
But you're violent, trained, dangerous.

1362
01:50:53,021 --> 01:50:55,314
You're the most dangerous patient
we have.

1363
01:50:55,398 --> 01:50:57,691
You've injured orderlies, guards,
other patients.

1364
01:50:57,775 --> 01:50:59,693
Two weeks ago,
you attacked George Noyce.

1365
01:50:59,777 --> 01:51:02,029
No, no. I am fucking on to you, Doctor.

1366
01:51:02,113 --> 01:51:03,989
- You had Noyce beaten.
- Of course I didn't!

1367
01:51:04,073 --> 01:51:06,158
Give me one reason
why I would even touch him!

1368
01:51:06,242 --> 01:51:08,619
Because he called you Laeddis,

1369
01:51:08,703 --> 01:51:11,747
and you'd do anything not to be him.

1370
01:51:11,831 --> 01:51:15,417
I have a transcript of the conversation
you had with Noyce yesterday.

1371
01:51:15,501 --> 01:51:19,546
"This is about you, and, Laeddis,
that's all it's ever been about."

1372
01:51:21,466 --> 01:51:23,967
No, no. He's saying
this is about me and Laeddis.

1373
01:51:24,052 --> 01:51:25,928
When you asked him
what happened to his face,

1374
01:51:26,012 --> 01:51:29,389
he said, now here I'm quoting again,
"You did this."

1375
01:51:29,474 --> 01:51:31,600
No, no, he meant that it was my fault.

1376
01:51:31,684 --> 01:51:33,685
You almost killed him.

1377
01:51:35,355 --> 01:51:38,148
The warden and the Board of Overseers
are determined something be done.

1378
01:51:38,233 --> 01:51:39,942
It's been decided

1379
01:51:40,026 --> 01:51:44,655
that unless we can bring you
back to sanity now, right now,

1380
01:51:44,739 --> 01:51:48,158
permanent measures will be taken to
ensure you can't hurt anyone ever again.

1381
01:51:51,663 --> 01:51:54,998
They'll lobotomize you, Andrew.
Do you understand?

1382
01:51:59,254 --> 01:52:01,171
Yeah, I understand.

1383
01:52:02,006 --> 01:52:04,216
I understand just fine.

1384
01:52:04,842 --> 01:52:08,929
If I don't play along
with your little game here,

1385
01:52:09,013 --> 01:52:12,140
Dr. Naehring's gonna turn me
into one of his ghosts.

1386
01:52:12,600 --> 01:52:13,976
But what about my partner?

1387
01:52:14,060 --> 01:52:18,522
You gonna tell the U.S. Marshal's office
that he's a defense mechanism?

1388
01:52:20,400 --> 01:52:21,858
Hello, boss.

1389
01:52:38,710 --> 01:52:41,503
What the fuck is going on here?

1390
01:52:44,382 --> 01:52:48,010
You working for him?

1391
01:52:48,845 --> 01:52:50,345
I'm sorry. There wasn't any other way.

1392
01:52:50,430 --> 01:52:53,348
Someone had to stick with you,
keep you safe.

1393
01:52:56,227 --> 01:52:58,353
You been watching me, huh?

1394
01:52:59,314 --> 01:53:01,398
Watching me every minute.

1395
01:53:02,317 --> 01:53:05,319
Who are you? Who are you? Tell me.

1396
01:53:06,112 --> 01:53:08,113
Don't you recognize me, Andrew?

1397
01:53:09,532 --> 01:53:13,243
I've been your primary psychiatrist
for the last two years.

1398
01:53:13,828 --> 01:53:15,704
I'm Lester Sheehan.

1399
01:53:22,170 --> 01:53:24,838
- I told you... I told you about my wife, I...
- I know.

1400
01:53:24,922 --> 01:53:28,175
I climbed down a cliff to get you.
I trusted you.

1401
01:53:28,259 --> 01:53:31,887
I risked everything to come
in here after you. Everything!

1402
01:53:31,971 --> 01:53:33,013
I know, boss.

1403
01:53:33,097 --> 01:53:35,891
We're running out of time here, Andrew.

1404
01:53:36,267 --> 01:53:37,851
I swore before the Board of Overseers

1405
01:53:37,935 --> 01:53:41,855
that I could construct the most radical,
cutting-edge role-play

1406
01:53:41,939 --> 01:53:44,191
ever attempted in psychiatry,
and it would bring you back.

1407
01:53:44,275 --> 01:53:47,319
I thought that if we let you play this out

1408
01:53:47,403 --> 01:53:51,031
we could get you to see
how untrue, how impossible it is.

1409
01:53:52,116 --> 01:53:54,576
You've had the run of the place
for two days.

1410
01:53:54,660 --> 01:53:57,954
Tell me, where are
the Nazi experiments?

1411
01:53:58,039 --> 01:53:59,831
The satanic ORs?

1412
01:54:13,471 --> 01:54:15,347
Andrew, listen to me.

1413
01:54:17,725 --> 01:54:19,976
If we fail with you,

1414
01:54:20,061 --> 01:54:23,980
then everything that we've tried to do
here will be discredited. Everything.

1415
01:54:26,109 --> 01:54:29,277
We're on the front lines
of a war here, old boy.

1416
01:54:30,029 --> 01:54:32,906
And right now, it all comes down to you.

1417
01:54:39,831 --> 01:54:42,541
- Don't move! Don't move!
- Andrew! Andrew! No. No.

1418
01:54:42,625 --> 01:54:45,836
My name is Edward Daniels!

1419
01:54:45,920 --> 01:54:47,963
This one's loaded.
I can tell by the weight.

1420
01:54:48,047 --> 01:54:50,632
I see. And that's your firearm, Marshal?
You're sure?

1421
01:54:50,716 --> 01:54:51,925
My initials are on the side.

1422
01:54:52,009 --> 01:54:54,302
There's a dent in the barrel
from when Philip Stacks shot at me.

1423
01:54:54,387 --> 01:54:56,513
You're not gonna fuck with my mind
on this one, Doctor!

1424
01:54:56,597 --> 01:54:57,639
Then blast away.

1425
01:54:57,723 --> 01:55:01,059
Because that's the only way
you're ever getting off this island.

1426
01:55:07,150 --> 01:55:09,025
Andrew, please don't.

1427
01:55:19,912 --> 01:55:21,204
My gun.

1428
01:55:27,795 --> 01:55:30,380
What did you do to my goddamn gun?

1429
01:55:30,798 --> 01:55:31,965
It's a toy, Andrew.

1430
01:55:35,470 --> 01:55:37,554
We're telling you the truth.

1431
01:55:38,055 --> 01:55:41,308
Dolores was insane,
manic-depressive, suicidal.

1432
01:55:41,976 --> 01:55:45,061
You drank, stayed away,
ignored what everyone told you.

1433
01:55:45,146 --> 01:55:46,271
You moved to that lake house

1434
01:55:46,355 --> 01:55:49,483
after she purposely set
your city apartment on fire.

1435
01:55:49,567 --> 01:55:50,859
- You were...
- You're lying.

1436
01:55:50,943 --> 01:55:54,404
- Andrew! Andrew, stop. No.
- You drugged the cigarettes!

1437
01:55:54,489 --> 01:55:56,323
- All you've done is lie!
- Andrew. Andrew.

1438
01:55:56,407 --> 01:55:59,618
Your children. Andrew, your children.

1439
01:55:59,702 --> 01:56:02,370
Simon. Henry.

1440
01:56:02,747 --> 01:56:04,039
I never had any children.

1441
01:56:04,123 --> 01:56:08,168
Your wife drowned them
at the cabin by the lake.

1442
01:56:08,252 --> 01:56:11,463
And here, the little girl,
the one you dream of

1443
01:56:12,173 --> 01:56:13,840
every night.

1444
01:56:13,925 --> 01:56:15,091
I never had a little girl.

1445
01:56:15,176 --> 01:56:18,762
The one who tells you over and over
that you should have saved her,

1446
01:56:18,846 --> 01:56:20,764
saved them all.

1447
01:56:20,848 --> 01:56:23,308
Your daughter, her name was Rachel.

1448
01:56:23,392 --> 01:56:26,269
Are you going to deny
that she ever lived?

1449
01:56:27,021 --> 01:56:28,772
Andrew, are you?

1450
01:56:51,754 --> 01:56:53,838
I'm so sorry, baby.

1451
01:56:58,219 --> 01:57:00,595
I told you not to come in here.

1452
01:57:01,055 --> 01:57:05,016
I told you this would be the end of you.

1453
01:57:25,371 --> 01:57:26,705
I'm back!

1454
01:57:27,331 --> 01:57:30,083
We got him just outside of Oklahoma.

1455
01:57:30,167 --> 01:57:32,711
Must've stopped 10 places
in between here and Tulsa.

1456
01:57:32,795 --> 01:57:34,879
I could sleep for a week.

1457
01:57:38,843 --> 01:57:48,393
Dolores?

1458
01:57:53,190 --> 01:57:55,483
And he said, "Take up your bed
and walk." But God?

1459
01:57:55,568 --> 01:57:56,610
Dolores?

1460
01:57:56,694 --> 01:58:00,780
Then he said, "Take up your bed
and walk." Forgive sins, but God?

1461
01:58:11,042 --> 01:58:12,417
Dolores?

1462
01:58:37,735 --> 01:58:38,985
Baby,

1463
01:58:41,030 --> 01:58:42,906
why are you all wet?

1464
01:58:45,242 --> 01:58:46,785
I missed you.

1465
01:58:54,168 --> 01:58:55,835
I wanna go home.

1466
01:58:58,964 --> 01:59:00,465
You are home.

1467
01:59:05,638 --> 01:59:07,472
Where are the kids?

1468
01:59:11,519 --> 01:59:13,269
They're in school.

1469
01:59:17,441 --> 01:59:19,442
It's Saturday, honey.

1470
01:59:20,611 --> 01:59:22,821
School's not in on Saturday.

1471
01:59:25,449 --> 01:59:27,075
My school is.

1472
01:59:40,423 --> 01:59:41,965
Oh, my God.

1473
01:59:44,260 --> 01:59:45,719
Oh, my God!

1474
01:59:58,858 --> 02:00:01,568
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

1475
02:00:05,740 --> 02:00:07,323
Oh, my God, no.

1476
02:00:11,787 --> 02:00:13,496
Come on, come on.

1477
02:00:26,719 --> 02:00:29,846
No. No. Please, God.

1478
02:00:31,849 --> 02:00:35,643
Please, God, no! No!

1479
02:00:38,856 --> 02:00:50,366
No.

1480
02:01:34,745 --> 02:01:35,954
Baby.

1481
02:01:54,765 --> 02:01:57,267
Let's put them at the table, Andrew.

1482
02:01:58,102 --> 02:02:01,312
We'll dry them off.
We'll change their clothes.

1483
02:02:03,482 --> 02:02:05,608
They'll be our living dolls.

1484
02:02:09,947 --> 02:02:12,699
Tomorrow we can take them on a picnic.

1485
02:02:17,705 --> 02:02:22,208
If you ever loved me, Dolores,
please stop talking.

1486
02:02:28,799 --> 02:02:30,300
I love you.

1487
02:02:39,018 --> 02:02:40,602
Set me free.

1488
02:02:45,274 --> 02:02:46,691
Oh, baby.

1489
02:02:50,154 --> 02:02:52,071
We'll give them baths.

1490
02:02:55,326 --> 02:02:58,536
- I love you, baby.
- I love you, too.

1491
02:02:58,621 --> 02:03:00,413
- I love you so much.
- I love you so much.

1492
02:03:00,497 --> 02:03:02,248
I love you. I...

1493
02:03:26,106 --> 02:03:27,857
Oh, baby.

1494
02:03:33,822 --> 02:03:35,156
Andrew.

1495
02:03:37,201 --> 02:03:39,202
Andrew, can you hear me?

1496
02:03:39,495 --> 02:03:40,828
Rachel.

1497
02:03:41,705 --> 02:03:43,373
Rachel, Rachel.

1498
02:03:45,626 --> 02:03:46,918
Rachel?

1499
02:03:49,421 --> 02:03:50,880
Rachel who?

1500
02:03:53,759 --> 02:03:55,843
Rachel. Rachel Laeddis.

1501
02:03:57,012 --> 02:03:58,763
My daughter.

1502
02:04:02,351 --> 02:04:04,102
Why are you here?

1503
02:04:07,314 --> 02:04:08,856
Because I killed my wife.

1504
02:04:08,941 --> 02:04:11,067
And why did you do that?

1505
02:04:14,571 --> 02:04:17,740
Because she murdered our children,

1506
02:04:20,661 --> 02:04:22,078
and she told me to let her go.

1507
02:04:26,250 --> 02:04:29,419
- Who's Teddy Daniels?
- He doesn't exist.

1508
02:04:31,755 --> 02:04:34,215
Neither does Rachel Solando.
I made them up.

1509
02:04:34,299 --> 02:04:35,550
Why?

1510
02:04:36,885 --> 02:04:39,053
We need to hear you say it.

1511
02:04:44,852 --> 02:04:48,062
After she tried to kill herself
the first time,

1512
02:04:50,107 --> 02:04:52,066
Dolores told me she...

1513
02:04:53,027 --> 02:04:57,280
She had an insect living
inside her brain.

1514
02:04:59,283 --> 02:05:03,995
She could feel it
clicking across her skull,

1515
02:05:04,079 --> 02:05:08,291
just pulling the wires just for fun.

1516
02:05:11,962 --> 02:05:13,755
She told me that.

1517
02:05:15,215 --> 02:05:18,051
She told me that, but I didn't listen.

1518
02:05:21,764 --> 02:05:24,057
I loved her so much, you know.

1519
02:05:25,476 --> 02:05:27,643
Why did you make them up?

1520
02:05:29,730 --> 02:05:33,649
Because I can't take knowing
that Dolores killed our children.

1521
02:05:37,488 --> 02:05:38,821
And I...

1522
02:05:41,325 --> 02:05:45,828
I killed them 'cause I didn't get her help,
you know.

1523
02:05:50,042 --> 02:05:51,667
I killed them.

1524
02:05:56,465 --> 02:05:57,590
Here's my fear, Andrew.

1525
02:05:57,674 --> 02:06:00,885
We broke through once before,
nine months ago,

1526
02:06:00,969 --> 02:06:01,969
and then you regressed.

1527
02:06:04,515 --> 02:06:07,850
- I don't remember that.
- I know.

1528
02:06:09,353 --> 02:06:11,145
You reset, Andrew.

1529
02:06:11,605 --> 02:06:15,691
Like a tape playing over and over
on an endless loop.

1530
02:06:16,944 --> 02:06:18,402
I hope that what we've done here
will be enough

1531
02:06:18,487 --> 02:06:21,614
to stop it from ever happening again,

1532
02:06:21,698 --> 02:06:25,201
but I need to know
you've accepted reality.

1533
02:06:31,708 --> 02:06:34,460
You came after me, huh, Doctor?

1534
02:06:36,338 --> 02:06:40,216
You tried to help me
when no one else would.

1535
02:06:52,020 --> 02:06:54,897
My name's Andrew Laeddis,

1536
02:07:01,905 --> 02:07:05,366
and I murdered my wife
in the spring of '52.

1537
02:07:30,100 --> 02:07:33,561
- How we doing this morning?
- Good.

1538
02:07:33,645 --> 02:07:36,564
- And you?
- Can't complain.

1539
02:07:46,241 --> 02:07:50,203
- So what's our next move?
- You tell me.

1540
02:07:55,792 --> 02:08:00,087
We gotta get off this rock, Chuck.
Get back to the mainland.

1541
02:08:00,172 --> 02:08:03,132
Whatever the hell's going on here,
it's bad.

1542
02:08:25,072 --> 02:08:28,282
Don't worry, partner,
they're not gonna catch us.

1543
02:08:33,830 --> 02:08:36,666
That's right. We're too smart for them.

1544
02:08:37,793 --> 02:08:39,919
Yeah, we are, aren't we?

1545
02:08:55,560 --> 02:08:58,312
You know,
this place makes me wonder...

1546
02:08:58,855 --> 02:09:00,940
Yeah, what's that, boss?

1547
02:09:01,900 --> 02:09:03,859
Which would be worse,

1548
02:09:04,695 --> 02:09:08,823
to live as a monster
or to die as a good man?

1549
02:09:18,667 --> 02:09:19,959
Teddy?

